&lt;p&gt;(% setting: nouvel_onglet/test %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% dyXMLTable filename:/data/xml/test.xml %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% searchform %)&lt;br /&gt;
	(% searchresults %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Search Widgets for data creating and calculation uses fields from plugin i18n_specialpages and names of the specialized classes from the page HTML structure. To display Search Widgets element on the necessary page insert the following line of code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets&amp;nbsp;parameters_list&amp;nbsp;%)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add the desired filter or filters group use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addFilter=&quot;specialfield&quot; mode=&quot;filter mode&quot; itemCaption=&quot;Your Item Caption&quot; caption=&quot;Your Block Caption&quot; showCounters=1 %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To put a Search Widgets items on the sidebar or in the template (e.g. the header of the page), use the following code (&quot;laptops-item&quot; is a special page name from which data will be collected):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?php get_search_widgets(array(&#039;specialName&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;laptops-items&#039;, &#039;addFilter&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;manufacturer&#039;, &#039;mode&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;dropdown&#039;, &#039;caption&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;Trademarks&#039;, &#039;showCounters&#039;=&amp;gt;1)); ?&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add a filter by price range use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addRange=1 caption=&quot;Your Block Caption&quot; currencySign=&quot;$&quot; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add page numbering (Pagination) use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addPagify=1 showItemsNumber=1 showPagesNumber=1 %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To insert the prepared sorting drop-down list (Sort by) use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addSort=&quot;price,asc,number&amp;amp;price,desc,number&quot; sortCaptions=&quot;Cheapest&amp;amp;Expensive&quot; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To insert the search input box use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addSearchBox=&quot;item-title&quot; Placeholder=&quot;Search by title&quot; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To form the contents of a catalog, use i18n_search function&amp;nbsp;searchresults. Parameter live=1 is necessary. Search Widgets uses its own page numbering function (Pagination) so remove i18n_search plugin numbering or change this parameter to the appropriate size (eg. 100). Searchresults form call could look like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% searchresults addTags=_parent_laptops live=1 lang=en HEADER=&#039;&#039; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Search Widgets requires following plugins activation on your site:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% searchform %)&lt;br /&gt;
	(% searchresults %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Search Widgets for data creating and calculation uses fields from plugin i18n_specialpages and names of the specialized classes from the page HTML structure. To display Search Widgets element on the necessary page insert the following line of code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets&amp;nbsp;parameters_list&amp;nbsp;%)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add the desired filter or filters group use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addFilter=&quot;specialfield&quot; mode=&quot;filter mode&quot; itemCaption=&quot;Your Item Caption&quot; caption=&quot;Your Block Caption&quot; showCounters=1 %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To put a Search Widgets items on the sidebar or in the template (e.g. the header of the page), use the following code (&quot;laptops-item&quot; is a special page name from which data will be collected):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?php get_search_widgets(array(&#039;specialName&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;laptops-items&#039;, &#039;addFilter&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;manufacturer&#039;, &#039;mode&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;dropdown&#039;, &#039;caption&#039;=&amp;gt;&#039;Trademarks&#039;, &#039;showCounters&#039;=&amp;gt;1)); ?&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add a filter by price range use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addRange=1 caption=&quot;Your Block Caption&quot; currencySign=&quot;$&quot; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To add page numbering (Pagination) use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addPagify=1 showItemsNumber=1 showPagesNumber=1 %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To insert the prepared sorting drop-down list (Sort by) use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addSort=&quot;price,asc,number&amp;amp;price,desc,number&quot; sortCaptions=&quot;Cheapest&amp;amp;Expensive&quot; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To insert the search input box use this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% get_search_widgets addSearchBox=&quot;item-title&quot; Placeholder=&quot;Search by title&quot; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To form the contents of a catalog, use i18n_search function&amp;nbsp;searchresults. Parameter live=1 is necessary. Search Widgets uses its own page numbering function (Pagination) so remove i18n_search plugin numbering or change this parameter to the appropriate size (eg. 100). Searchresults form call could look like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% searchresults addTags=_parent_laptops live=1 lang=en HEADER=&#039;&#039; %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Search Widgets requires following plugins activation on your site:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(% searchform %)&lt;br /&gt;
	(% searchresults %)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

